text: 81st St, at the S.W. corner of 34th Avenue showing Fillmore Hall, a group of new apartment houses. On the right is the 34th Avenue side of the buildings. About 1927. Brown Brothers.

81st Street (left), east side, north from 34th Avenue to Northern Boulevard, showing a group of apartment buildings called "The Towers." These buildings are also on the west side of 82nd Street and extend as far north as Northern Boulevard. The 34th Avenue side of the two corner buildings are also shown. The avenue has a tree-lined isle. About 1928. Ewing Galloway.

81st Street, at the N.E. corner of 34th Avenue, showing a corner of "The Towers," a large group of apartment houses. The view is eastward across tennis courts lying between 79th and 80th Streets.

Brown Brothers

About 1928
